{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-manage-shop-by-brand-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Manage Shop by Brand in Magento 2","content":"\n<p>Online store owners widely use <a href=\"https://business.adobe.com/in/products/magento/open-source.html\">Magento 2</a> as an e-commerce platform to efficiently manage their businesses. It offers a range of features and functionalities that enhance the online shopping experience for customers. Among its features is the &#8220;Shop by Brand&#8221; option, which helps online stores categorize their products by brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This blog post provides a detailed guide on how to manage the &#8220;Shop by Brand&#8221; feature in Magento 2. It covers various aspects such as creating brand categories, assigning products to specific brands, and customizing brand pages&#8217; display. This comprehensive guide aims on <strong><em>How to Manage Shop by Brand in Magento 2</em></strong>, thereby enhancing their customers&#8217; shopping experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Steps to Manage Shop by Brand in Magneto 2</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Install the Brand Extension</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To manage your store by brand in Magento 2, you will first need to <a href=\"https://meetanshi.com/magento-2-shop-by-brand.html\">install a brand extension</a>. There are several extensions available in the Magento Marketplace, including Amasty&#8217;s Shop by Brand and Aheadworks&#8217; Shop by Brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 2: Create a Brand Attribute</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have installed the brand extension, you will need to create a brand attribute. This attribute will be used to categorize your products by brand. To create a brand attribute, navigate to Stores > Attributes > Product and click on the Add New Attribute button. Fill in the necessary information, such as the attribute code and label, and select the Catalog Input Type for Store Owner as Dropdown.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained  inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:624px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;291&#x27;%20width=&#x27;624&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 624px) 624px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/bac30dbdbccaee901c70f7b750ddbd7d/2f13b806c3a55e7c70077beb88f375d0/how-to-manage-shop-by-brand-in-magento-2.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2Fhow-to-manage-shop-by-brand-in-magento-2.png&amp;a=w%3D156%26h%3D73%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-20T04%3A12%3A45\" data-srcset=\"/_gatsby/image/bac30dbdbccaee901c70f7b750ddbd7d/2f13b806c3a55e7c70077beb88f375d0/how-to-manage-shop-by-brand-in-magento-2.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2Fhow-to-manage-shop-by-brand-in-magento-2.png&amp;a=w%3D156%26h%3D73%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-20T04%3A12%3A45 156w,/_gatsby/image/bac30dbdbccaee901c70f7b750ddbd7d/dc64605831263dcce1653475e2134a4f/how-to-manage-shop-by-brand-in-magento-2.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2Fhow-to-manage-shop-by-brand-in-magento-2.png&amp;a=w%3D312%26h%3D145%26f